    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Reproducible in release-20170421.\r\nIt happens when you have many players (more than 20 ?) and many actors (hundreds ?) on the map.\r\nSimply set the replay speed to MAX and wait, the game will freeze (the actors on the map, not the game itself : you can continue to use the minimap, the menu, and you can exit the game, nothing crashes).\r\nExample of replay freezing at 15:35 ~~at MAX speed~~ : [https://ufile.io/p91gt](https://ufile.io/p91gt).\r\n\r\n__Edit__ : this replay also freezes at 15:35 if you watch it at a speed of 100 % so this bug comes from the replay itself and not from the replay speed.\r\nIf you watch it at a MAX speed it freezes at 15:35.\r\nIf you watch it at a speed of 100 % it becomes Paused at 15:35 and you can't unpause it.\r\n\r\n__Edit 2__ (100 % speed version) : after waiting something like five minutes the replay auto-unpauses itself and continues.\r\n(The replay file has not been modified or touched in any manner)\r\n\r\n__Edit 3__ : OK I figured it out. ðŸŽ‰  Forget everything above.\r\nIf you watch a 100 % AI game as a spectator, and if you press Esc during the game to go in the menu, which actually __pauses__ the game, then OpenRA saves that pause in the replay. ðŸ˜† \r\nI don't know why \"Paused\" is not written in the UI when the replay is played at MAX speed though."
